The speed of sound gets slower as the atmospheric pressure gets thinner, because there are fewer particles to vibrate (sound is just a vibration) think of it as a relay race where you have to squeeze someone’s hand. You have to get the high-five one kilometer. If there are a lot of people, you can pass the hand-squeeze through them. If there are fewer people, you have to walk all the way to the next person to pass on the hand-squeeze. The people are molecules (it doesn’t have to be air) and the hand-squeezes are vibrations. That’s why the speed of sound is so much slower with little atmosphere. With none, the speed of sound is stationary.
